" data-component-name="MentionToDOM"></span> suggested that I read Elisabeth Tova Bailey&#8217;s <em><a href="https://geni.us/OlQ37">The Sound of a Wild Snail Eating</a></em>, a marvelous little book about a bedridden woman who observes a snail while she slowly convalesces from a debilitating illness. The snail becomes her companion and a kind of muse: </p>
